The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Tata Tele targets more from rights

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 16: Tata Teleservices Maharashtra Ltd (TTML) today increased the size of its rights issue to Rs 500 crore from the previous Rs 329 crore that was approved by the board on December 22, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. However, the issue price is yet to be announced which was earlier fixed at Rs 25-27 per share, inclusive of premium.

 According to the previous announcement, the entitlement ratio was 2 shares for every 25 shares held but the revised entitlement is being worked out, the company said. In January, TTML filed the offer letter for the rights issue to mobilise funds to meet its ongoing requirements.

 Although the exact number of shares to be divested is not clear, Tata Group firms collectively own 65.53 per cent of the issued and paid-up equity capital of the company, including Tata Teleservices Ltd (TTSL), which owns 47 per cent of the issued and paid-up equity capital of TTML.

 Under the terms of the loans availed of by the company, TTSL has pledged its shareholding in favour of the lenders and has also undertaken that the percentage of shares pledged by it would not be less than 50.83 per cent of our total subscribed equity shares (subject to any dilution as a result of exercise of employee stock options), the company had said in the draft offer letter. 

 Tata Teleservices Maharashtra has suffered a net loss of Rs 527.86 crore in 2004-05. 

 Last fiscal, the companys performance improved as it reported a total income of Rs 1,096.79 crore, a 31 per cent rise over Rs 836.48 crore recorded in the previous year. 

 For the fourth quarter, the company achieved a cash profit of Rs 26 crore compared with a cash loss of Rs 69 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. 




